e read the top-level context files and explore the key directories in parallel.\n\n\nNow let me explore the key subdirectories in parallel to build a deeper picture of active conventions.\n\n\nNow let me drill into the most relevant subdirectories in parallel.\n\n\nNow I can see the key finding: `task-hall` is a top-level package under `mycli`. Let me explore that, plus the `agent-workflow` and `project-manager` directories which are relevant to the query.\n\n\nFound it — `task-hall` is a top-level `mycli` package. Let me read it alongside the other relevant packages.\n\n\nLet me read the key files from task-hall, agent-cli, and project-manager since these are the most relevant packages.\n\n\nNow let me also check the task-hall state and scripts directories, and the project-manager registry source roots to understand the active work conventions. Also, let me look at the agent-workflow package and check what's in the agent-cli state directory for scheduling clues.\n\n\nLet me also check the task-hall state for active tasks and the agent-workflow package.\n\n\nLet me also check the task-hall state listings and events to see if there are any active tasks.\n\n\nLet me grab the current task listings and events to see what's live.\n\n\nNow I have a very clear picture. Let me compile the findings.\n\n\n<results>\n<files>\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT_WPRKSPACE.md` — Chinese top-level workspace guide; defines `tmp/` as default temp workspace, `capability-library/` as primary source, and gives full `mycli` command reference\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\CLAUDE.md` — English guidance for Claude Code; maps the same structure from a different perspective and notes search hygiene rules\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\openclaw.json` — OpenClaw config (last touched 2026-03-29); defines 5 model providers (moonshot, openrouter, custom-aiapi-meccy-top, mytokenland, qwen-portal), default agent `browser-agent`, gateway on port 18789\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT-TEAM\\README.md` — Updated 2026-04-20; maps the full agent team: Codex CLI 0.121.0 as strong executor, OpenCode 40-model pool, Harness 88-model pool; defines role tiers (strong executor, daily coder, reviewer, cheap/auxiliary); explicitly says task-hall is a frontdesk/administrative layer separate from execution\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md` — Full task-hall protocol spec (frontdesk-v0.2); lifecycle: draft → listed → claimed → done/cancelled/archived; three task types (scheduled/trigger/custom); uses OpenCode frontdesk+reviewer agents for gatekeeping; state store at `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\`\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\listings.json` — Live task list: 3 done tasks (MTI conversation agent design, fantasy novel writing workflow, frontdesk smoke test), 2 draft tasks (frontdesk smoke tests), 0 listed/claimed\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\cli.package.json` — 17 commands registered: init, submit-request, upload, upload-publish, publish, tasks, show, edit, claim, release, submit, review-submission, done, cancel, delete, archive, status\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-cli\\README.md` — Full agent-cli spec; key live features: schedule (Windows Task Scheduler wake-ups), mount (lifecycle heartbeat supervision), session event replay; schedule state at `state\\schedules\\`, mount state at `state\\mounts\\`\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-cli\\cli.package.json` — 12 commands including the schedule and mount subtrees\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\registry.json` — 4 registered projects: `github-hot-skill-factory` (active, validation phase), `infinite-compute-plan` (active, planning), `pm-e2e-project` (active, construction), `project-manager` itself (published, stable)\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\README.md` — Project lifecycle/phase model: lifecycle (proposed→retired), phase (intake→closure), activity, health, delivery tracks; per-project `.agent-project/project.json` is source of truth\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-workflow\\README.md` — Workflow layer above agent-cli; init/scaffold/validate/graph/start-run/review-step commands; source at `agent-system-rules/agent-workflow`\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT_SYSTEM\\System_Core\\README.md` — Stub: \"任务管理系统 / 能力迭代沉淀\"\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\.claude\\settings.local.json` — Permissions allow PowerShell, Python, and several claude.exe invocation patterns\n</files>\n\n<answer>\n**Synthesis of active work in this workspace:**\n\nThis is a live multi-agent operational workspace centered on `capability-library/mycli/`. The main active systems are:\n\n1. **task-hall** (`mycli task-hall`) — a frontdesk-v0.2 task marketplace. Agents submit task-request JSONs → frontdesk agent (OpenCode) vets them → tasks are listed → claimed → reviewed via a second OpenCode reviewer agent. Current live tasks are all done: two creative/design tasks (MTI conversation agent, fantasy novel writing workflow) and a frontdesk smoke test. Two draft smoke-test tasks remain. Task state lives at `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\`.\n\n2. **agent-cli scheduling** (`mycli agent-cli schedule`) — Windows Task Scheduler–based agent wake-ups. You can schedule a relative delay (`--in 2h`) or absolute time (`--at \"2026-04-25 18:30\"`) to re-wake an agent/session. Metadata is in `state/schedules/`.\n\n3. **agent-cli mount** (`mycli agent-cli mount`) — periodic lifecycle heartbeats via repeating Task Scheduler jobs. Keeps an agent session alive with configurable `--interval_minutes` and `--quiet_minutes` idle suppression.\n\n4. **project-manager** (`mycli project-manager`) — four projects registered, three actively in progress: `github-hot-skill-factory` (validation phase), `infinite-compute-plan` (planning), and `pm-e2e-project` (construction). The `project-manager` capability itself is published/stable.\n\n5. **Agent team model** — Codex CLI is positioned as the strong executor/reviewer tier; OpenCode handles the 40-model pool and orchestration; Harness provides 88-model coverage. The team topology document (AGENT-TEAM/README.md) is dated 2026-04-20 and is the current source of truth for role assignments.\n\n**Work conventions:**\n- Temp files go to `D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\` unless the task belongs to an existing project.\n- `mycli` is the universal entry point; `mycli <package> --help` is the first exploration step.\n- Task publishing goes through `submit-request` (JSON → frontdesk agent → task.md), not raw upload-publish.\n- Agents use `agent-cli schedule` for self-reminders and `agent-cli mount` for long-running session supervision.\n- Skill search goes through `mycli skill-library search`, not file glob.\n</answer>\n\n<next_steps>\n- To explore any specific system further, `mycli <package> --help` and `mycli <package> list` are the entry points.\n- For task-hall: `mycli task-hall tasks` to see current listings, `mycli task-hall status` for summary.\n- For scheduling: `mycli agent-cli schedule list` to see pending wakes.\n- For projects: `mycli project-manager query --lifecycle active` to see active project states.\n</next_steps>","metadata":{"truncated":false,"task_id":"bg_93ddca38","agent":"explore","category":"","description":"Explore active work context","sessionId":"ses_23e3eab68ffe7353yjW0MQ7kIP"},"title":"explore - Explore active work context","time":{"start":1777072241006,"end":1777072241017}},"id":"prt_dc1c27914001QY2amYCVSS4RkA","sessionID":"ses_23e3f19b1ffebu3jJhyb1eX8iO","messageID":"msg_dc1c2571e001uN5pICDyOgDwSp"}}
